<doc id="403801" wikidata="Q3135653" url="?curid=403801" title="Hildegard">
<text>Hildegard is a female name derived from the Old High German &quot;hild&quot; (&#x27;war&#x27; or &#x27;battle&#x27;) and &quot;gard&quot; (&#x27;enclosure&#x27; or &#x27;yard&#x27;), and means &#x27;battle enclosure&#x27;. Variant spellings include: Hildegarde; the Polish, Portuguese, Slovene and Spanish Hildegarda; the Italian Ildegarda; the Hungarian Hildegárd; and the ancient German Hildegardis.

