<doc id="403803" wikidata="Q7874587" url="?curid=403803" title="USS Tallahassee">
<text>Only one ship of the United States Navy has been named USS &quot;Tallahassee&quot;, after the city of Tallahassee, Florida, but two others were projected to carry the name.

* The first was an monitor used as a submarine tender during World War I, originally named USS &quot;Florida&quot; and later redesignated IX-16.
* The second was converted from a light cruiser to the before launching.
* The third was a light cruiser that was cancelled before launching.</text><links>
